\begin_layout Standard
Negative of a vector is a vector of the same magnitude whose direction is
 flipped by 
\begin_inset Formula $180^{\text{o}}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Addition and subtraction of vectors
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Graphical addition of vectors is carried out by placing the tail of the
 second vector on to the head of the first vector.
 Consider two vectors 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{A}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{B}$
\end_inset

, then the sum of these vectors 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{C}=\boldsymbol{A}+\boldsymbol{B}$
\end_inset

 is done as followingly 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
placement H
wide false
sideways false
